# Windsurf Rules — Solar Navigator

## Project Identity
Solar Navigator is an **AI agent coding experiment**. Every feature is co-created with AI
coding agents; the human author's role is to direct and review, not write code manually.
Write clean, idiomatic Rust that future agents can extend with minimal context.

## Tech Stack
- Rust 2024 edition · Bevy 0.18.1 · bevy_egui · wgpu v27
- Optional `spice` feature: `rust-spice` wrapping NAIF CSPICE C library
- `reqwest` for NASA JPL Horizons HTTP queries
- Custom WGSL shader: `assets/shaders/planet_atmosphere.wgsl`

## Source Layout
```
src/
  main.rs / ephemeris.rs          — entry point and ephemeris logic (no Bevy)
  app/mod.rs                      — Bevy App, resources, system registration
  app/types.rs                    — all Resources, Components, BODIES constant
  app/setup.rs                    — Startup systems (scene, textures, sync)
  app/simulation.rs               — Update systems (input, time, positions)
  app/camera.rs                   — Update systems (orbit camera, fly-to)
  app/render.rs                   — Update systems (lighting, visibility)
  app/materials.rs                — atmosphere shader material
  app/ui.rs                       — egui side panel
  app/util.rs                     — helpers (asset path, image, formatting)
```

## Coding Rules
- Everything inside `app/` is `pub(super)` — no public API leaks out.
- Types/resources → `types.rs`. Systems → the module that logically owns them.
- `BODIES` in `types.rs` is the single source of truth for all 14 rendered bodies.
- Both Cargo feature variants must compile and lint cleanly at all times:
  - Default (SPICE): `cargo check --all-targets`
  - Portable: `cargo check --all-targets --no-default-features`
- `clippy -D warnings` enforced in CI. Every `#[allow]` needs a justification comment.
- No `unwrap()` in production paths — use `?`, `if let`, or `else { return }`.

## Coordinate System
SPICE `ECLIPJ2000` → Bevy Y-up:
- `scene_x = spice_x * scale`
- `scene_y = spice_z * scale`  (SPICE Z is ecliptic north → Bevy Y)
- `scene_z = -spice_y * scale` (negated to keep right-handed axes)

## Quick Build
```bash
cargo run --release --no-default-features   # always works
cargo run --release                         # needs vendor/cspice
```
